name: Microbiology Homework - Chapter 26
description: Homework questions for Chapter 26 of the OpenStax Microbiology textbook.
subject: Microbiology

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The basic purpose is to coordinate all activities of the body.
questions.explanation: The image displays the nervous system, which coordinates all activities of the body.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: There are 5 main sections of the brain.
questions.explanation: The brain is typically divided into three main sections: the cerebrum, cerebellum, and brainstem.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The frontal lobe is responsible for integrating sensory information.
questions.explanation: The parietal lobe is responsible for integrating sensory information. The frontal lobe is involved in higher executive functions.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The hypothalamus plays a role in emotions such as anger and pleasure.
questions.explanation: The hypothalamus is a key part of the limbic system, which governs emotions.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The afferent neurons take information from the nerves to the peripheral nervous system.
questions.explanation: Afferent neurons (or sensory neurons) carry nerve impulses from sensory stimuli towards the central nervous system and brain.
